Description:
    This package provides a modular and reproducible framework for the
    preprocessing and analysis of Illumina EPICv2 DNA methylation array 
    data. It supports quality control, probe filtering, cell-type 
    deconvolution, phenotype integration, and downstream statistical 
    modelling using generalised linear and linear mixed-effects models. 
    The package builds on established Bioconductor infrastructure and 
    wraps widely used tools such as 'minfi', 'ENmix', 'wateRmelon', and 
    'ewastools', with support for execution on local workstations and 
    high-performance computing environments.
